The Moldova Nou mine is a large mine in the west of Romania in Cara-Severin County, 93km southwest of Reia and 579km north-west of the capital, Bucharest. Moldova Nou represents the second largest copper reserve in Romania having estimated reserves of 500 million tonnes of ore grading 0.35% copper.[1] 
